). Turn off oven and leave meringue in oven to cool for 1 hour. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Passionfruit curd"},{"content":"Strain passionfruit pulp through a fine-mesh sieve into a jug. Reserve any remaining pulp and seeds."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place passionfruit juice, orange juice, sugar, butter and eggs into mixing bowl and cook <b>8 min\/80°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Check to see if mixture has reached setting point by inserting a spoon into curd. Curd should coat the back of the spoon in a thick layer. If curd is not set, cook for a further <b>2-3 min\/80°C\/speed 3<b>, or until thickened. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>."},{"content":"Transfer curd into a sealable jar or container and set aside to cool to room temperature, then place into refrigerator until cold. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <b>30-40 sec\/speed 4<b>, or until soft peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>."},{"content":"To assemble, dollop  2-3 teaspoons passionfruit curd and 2-3 teaspoons whipped cream onto 6 serving plates in any pattern you like. Break meringue into shards and decorate each plate with 1-2 meringue pieces. Garnish with orange segments, mint leaves and reserved passionfruit pulp and seeds. Serve immediately."}],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","2h 50m","6 portions"]}